The corrected proof relies entirely on basic ideal properties and the definition of intersection. The `cases` tactic was not necessary for `zero_mem'`, but it was kept for uniformity with the `add_mem'` proof. The use of `hx.1`, `hx.2`, etc., directly mirrors the structure of the intersection, making it easy to follow. The proof does not require `aesop`, `simp_all`, or any other heavy tactics, confirming its simplicity and correctness. 

